Heard a LOT about the food here, so since I am a "foodie", I took the hour drive from LI to check it out. I was very disappointed and a little sad. The fried rice was decent (just like home cooked fried rice, which is fine) but the 4 or 5 little pieces of chicken (more like scraps) that came with it was not nearly enough compared to other Guyanese West Indian restaurants. The duck curry ($12.95) was terrible.  No distinctive taste whatsoever !!! I also read about the Black Pudding (Lamb) being good, so I tried an order ($10.95) which was typical of any other place, except more money here !! Clearly this is NOT made there, but catered from somewhere else !! The Pork Lo Mein was just bland !!! The Goat curry was ok, but the goat was clearly not "washed" well before cooking... Just a waste of time and money !!! Chef Quang should be more like Chef Quan't !!
